HEADWORD: Heddling
<hw>Hed"dling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>vb. n.</pos> <def>The act of
drawing the warp threads through the heddle-eyes of a weaver's harness;
the harness itself.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
